Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve any large @broccoli florets{200}(halved if large) and pop onto a #baking tray{} with the @British chicken breast{260%g}(diced), (use another tray if necessary).

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until the chicken is slightly golden, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

In the meantime, bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the rigatoni.

When boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest and halve the @lemon{1}(zested and halved).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the lemon zest, @chilli flakes{1}(or less if you'd prefer things milder), @panko breadcrumbs{25g} and half the garlic. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and fry, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch it like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Once cooked, transfer the zesty garlic crumb to a #bowl{} and set aside.

Return the (now empty) frying pan to medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Add the remaining garlic and stir-fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @water{100%ml} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Simmer until thickened slightly, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir through the @hard Italian style cheese{20%g}(grated), cooked pasta and @peas{120%g}. Simmer until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add a squeeze of lemon juice and stir through. Taste and add more salt, pepper and lemon juice if needed.

Share the creamy pasta between your bowls and top with the roasted broccoli.

Finish by sprinkling over the zesty garlic crumb.

Enjoy!